The paper discusses the use of artificial neural networks and transfer learning techniques for financial applications, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of behavioural genetics and selective breeding, which could be categorized under computational evolution (cs.CE) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed approach on financial data, which could be categorized under social and information networks (cs.SI).
